
Board Certified Psychiatrist, Psychologist, Principle Investigator for Clinical Research
Health Sciences Assistant Clinical Professor, UC Davis Department of Psychiatry and Behavioral Sciences
Medical Director, Brainefit A New Path To Mental Wellness

Education: Research Track Residency in Psychiatry at University of Texas Southwestern Medical School, Ph.D. in Counseling Psychology from University of NebraskaLincoln, Medical Graduate from Beijing Medical University/Peking University.
Expertise: Comprehensive care from medication management, psychotherapy, repetitive Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation (rTMS) to other scientifically approved new techniques to treat mental disorders. Current research projects focus on cutting edge nonpharmacological treatment such as deep rTMS in treatment of different brain diseases.
Ongoing clinical studies in open recruitment of volunteers: 1. Randomized, doubleblind, shamcontrolled, phase III trial on safety and efficacy of deep rTMS in treatment of bipolardepression;  2. Randomized, doubleblind, shamcontrolled, phase III study of deep rTMS as an aid to smoking cessation.
